<section class="jumbotron">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="row">
      <div class="col-md-7">
        <div class="jumbotron-inner">
          <h1>Sheffield Obstetric Difficult Airway course</h1>
          <p class="lead">The Sheffield Obstetric Difficult Airway course, otherwise known as the SODA course, is an unique educational course.</p>
          <p> The course teaches advanced airway skills and explores human factors during emergency simulated scenarios.</p>
          <p> Our ultimate aim is to increase the safety of the obstetric patient during general anaesthesia.</p>
          <%= link_to "Find out more", "/index.html#theScheme", class: "btn btn-lg btn-headroom btn-success visible-xs visible-sm" %>
        </div>
      </div>
      
      <div class="col-md-4 col-md-offset-1">
        <div class="card card-colourful card-jumbotron hidden-xs hidden-sm">
          <h2>Apply now</h2>
          <p>
            Are you ready to gain the skills, knowledge and confidence to make real improvements to the NHS?
          </p>
          <a class="btn btn-block btn-wire" href="#apply">Apply now</a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="graduate-lead">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="row">
      <div class="col-md-12">
        <p class="lead">We're launching an exciting new graduate management scheme to grow and develop passionate, inspirational leaders of the future.</p>
        <p>Over two years, you'll gain the skills, knowledge and confidence that will enable you to make real improvements at the frontline of the healthcare service and improve patient care.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="graduate-about" id="about">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="row">      
      <div class="col-md-12">
        <h2 class="header-lg-space">About us</h2>
      </div>
      <div class="col-md-7">
        <p>We are one of the UK's biggest and most successful providers of hospital and community based healthcare.</p>
        <p>We provide comprehensive NHS services ranging from maternity services to care of the elderly. We provide services to Sheffield, South Yorkshire, Mid Yorkshire and North Derbyshire but also specialist services to all parts of the UK.</p>
        <p>We have a long history of providing high quality care, clinical excellence and innovation in medical research and we are proud to have been awarded an overall rating of ‘Good’ following the latest Care Quality Commission inspection.</p>
        <p>With around 16,500 employees working within our hospitals and out in the community, we are one of the biggest employers locally. We aim to reflect the diversity of local communities and are proud of our partnerships with local people, patients, neighbouring NHS organisations, local authority and charitable bodies.</p>
        <p>Through our partnerships with the University of Sheffield, Sheffield Hallam University, other health and social care providers and industry we remain at the forefront of advancements in clinical services, teaching and research.</p>
      </div>    
      <div class="col-md-5">
        <%= image_tag "infographic.jpg", class: "img-responsive" %>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>


<section class="graduate-scheme" id="theScheme">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="row">      
      <div class="col-md-12">
        <h2 class="header-lg-space">The scheme</h2>
      </div>
      
      <div class="col-md-7">
        <p>Our Graduate Management Scheme aims to develop individuals with potential into high calibre managers and leaders of the future.</p>
        
        <p>Joining the scheme will help you to develop the skills, behaviours, experiences and confidence you need to lead in a dynamic healthcare environment.</p>
        
        <p>During the scheme you will spend your time working alongside some of the most talented people in the NHS who will offers guidance and support.</p>

        <h4>Two year programme</h4>
        
        <p>The two year programme will offer you many exciting new experiences to help lead NHS services in Sheffield that improve the lives of millions of people. The scheme will provide you with the opportunity to develop both professionally and personally, and allow you to gain an understanding of where your career aspirations lie.</p>
        
        <p>During the two years, you will complete both an operational placement and a corporate placement. This will give you a feel for working both on the 'front line' and behind the scenes and you will see how they come together to deliver high quality care for our patients.</p>

        <p>Each work placement will differ depending on the department it is hosted by, and the duties aligned to the placement role. You can be assured that wherever you are placed within our complex and varied organisation, you will be presented with a broad range of exciting experiences and opportunities to develop your knowledge and skills whilst working alongside our passionate and committed staff.</p>

      </div>
      
      <div class="col-md-5">
        <%= image_tag "graduate_one_sm.jpg", class: "img-responsive img-footing" %>

        <div class="card card-colourful card-feature card-reasons">
          <h3>In numbers</h3>
          <ol class="list-unstyled list-featured">
            <li>
              <span class="mega">2</span> year course
            </li>
            
            <li>
              <span class="mega">£22K</span> starting salary
            </li>
            
            <li>
              <span class="mega">2:2</span> degree or above
            </li>
            
            <li>
              <span class="mega">27</span> days annual leave
            </li>
     
          </ol>

        </div>
      </div>
      
      <div class="col-md-12">
        <h2 class="header-lg-space">About you</h2>
      </div>
      
      <div class="col-md-7">
        
        <p>Doing the right thing for our patients, staff and the wider public is what drives us and we’ll expect you to share our values.</p>

        <p>We are seeking to recruit people that can demonstrate they have the necessary qualifications, skills, qualities and values that give them the potential to succeed in a leadership or managerial role within the NHS.</p>

        <p>We are committed to recruiting people from a range of different backgrounds and would particularly welcome applications from candidate’s underrepresented in leadership roles.</p>
        <p>Prior to applying for a place on the scheme, please download and read through the <a title="Graduate Scheme NHS Jobs description" href="http://www.jobs.nhs.uk/xi/vacancy/cd19a5d0ab59b46cb0bbb1f7abc4ac79/?vac_ref=914626268">Job Description and Person Specification for the role</a>.</p>
      </div>    
      <div class="col-md-5">
        <%= image_tag "graduate_two_sm.jpg", class: "img-responsive img-footing" %>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="graduate-apply" id="apply">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="row">      
      
      <div class="col-md-12">
        <h2 class="header-lg-space">Apply now</h2>
      </div>
      
      <div class="col-md-7">
        <p>More details about the graduate management scheme can be found in our <%= link_to "job description and person specification", "./documents/Sheffield Teaching Hospitals NHS Foundation Trust Graduate Management Scheme.pdf" %>.</p>
        <p>If you have any questions <a href="mailto:GraduateScheme@sth.nhs.uk">contact us by emailing GraduateScheme@sth.nhs.uk</a>.</p>
        <p>Please note that the 2 year programme will commence on 16 October 2017 and all successful candidates must be available to commence in post on this date.</p>
        <div class="card card-colourful card-feature card-cta img-footing">
          <h3 id="">Interested?</h3>
          <a class="btn btn-wire" href="http://www.jobs.nhs.uk/xi/vacancy/cd19a5d0ab59b46cb0bbb1f7abc4ac79/?vac_ref=914626268">Help shape the future of the NHS</a>
        </div>
      </div>
      
      <div class="col-md-4 col-md-offset-1">
        <% link_to "./documents/Sheffield Teaching Hospitals NHS Foundation Trust Graduate Management Scheme.pdf" do %>
          <%= image_tag "thumbnail.jpg", class: "img-responsive" %>
        <% end %>
        <div class="block">
          <%= link_to "Download booklet" , "./documents/Sheffield Teaching Hospitals NHS Foundation Trust Graduate Management Scheme.pdf"%>
        </div> 
      </div>
      
      <div class="col-md-12">
        <h2 class="header-lg-space">Application process</h2>
      </div>
      
      <div class="col-md-4">
        <h3 class="graduate-step" id="step1">1.</h3>
        <h4>Online application <span class="glyphicon glyphicon-graduate-menu" aria-hidden="true"></span></h4>
        <p>Your application must be submitted via <a href="http://www.jobs.nhs.uk/xi/vacancy/cd19a5d0ab59b46cb0bbb1f7abc4ac79/?vac_ref=914626268">the NHS Jobs by completing the online application form</a>. Candidates are encouraged to read the associated documentation prior to completing and submitting their application.</p>
        <p>Applications will be reviewed within 14 days from the advertisement being closed. If you successfully demonstrate how you meet the essential criteria you will be shortlisted to progress further through the application process.</p>
      </div>
      
      <div class="col-md-4">
        <h3 class="graduate-step" id="step2">2.</h3>
        <h4>Assessment centre <span class="glyphicon glyphicon-graduate-menu" aria-hidden="true"></span></h4>
        <p>Shortlisted candidates will progress through the selection process, including attendance at an assessment centre on the 14 July 2017.</p>
        <p>We will select 30 candidates to progress through to the assessment centre stage. During the assessment centre, participants will be required to complete a variety of exercises and will undergo a panel interview. </p>
      </div>
      
      <div class="col-md-4">
        <h3 class="graduate-step" id="step3">3.</h3>
        <h4>Pre-employment checks</h4>
        <p>Within 7 days of the assessment centre, the successful trainees will be informed that they have secured a conditional offer of a place on the graduate trainee management scheme. </p>
        <p>A programme of clearance checks will commence for the successful candidates and upon successful clearance through pre-employment checks your confirmed offer of employment will be made.</p>
      </div>
      
      <div class="col-md-12">
        <div class="card card-colourful card-feature card-cta">
          <h3 id="">Interested?</h3>
          <h4>Apply now</h4>
          <p>
            Gain the skills, knowledge and confidence to make real improvements to the NHS.
          </p>
          <a class="btn btn-wire" href="http://www.jobs.nhs.uk/xi/vacancy/cd19a5d0ab59b46cb0bbb1f7abc4ac79/?vac_ref=914626268">Help shape the future of the NHS</a>
        </div>
      </div>
      
    </div>
  </div>
</section>